<#ftl output_format="HTML">
<#include "../../macro/component/icon.ftl">

<div class="grid-row">
    <div class="column column--two-thirds">
        <div class="article-section article-section--summary">
            <h1>Button styles</h1>
            <p>Use buttons to help users carry out an action on a page like starting an application or saving their progress.</p>
            <p>Make sure the text you use describes the action. Write button text in sentence case and describe the action the button performs. For example "Save and continue" or "Start now".</p>
        </div>

        <div class="article-section article-section--summary">
            <h2>NHS digital button</h2>
            <pre><code>.cta-btn .cta-btn--blue</code></pre>
            <button class="cta-btn cta-btn--blue">Button</button>
            <ul>
                <li>Use a primary button to help users carry out an action on a page like starting an application or saving their progress.</li>
                <li>Align the primary action button to the left edge of your form.</li>
                <li>The colour contrast ratio between text and background colour is as follows: primary button 5.12:1</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="article-section article-section--summary">
            <h2>Journey Start Button</h2>
            <pre><code>.cta-btn .cta-btn--green</code></pre>
            <button class="cta-btn cta-btn--green">Button</button>
            <ul>
                <li>Use a Journey start button to help users carry out an action on a page like starting an application.</li>
                <li>The colour contrast ratio between text and background colour is as follows: primary button 5.12:1</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="article-section article-section--summary">
            <h2>Secondary Button</h2>
            <pre><code>.cta-btn .cta-btn--grey</code></pre>
            <button class="cta-btn cta-btn--grey">Button</button>
            <ul>
                <li>Use a secondary button on pages that have more than 1 action or when users aren't noticing standard link text.</li>
                <li>The colour contrast ratio between text and background colour is as follows: secondary button 7.75:1</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="article-section article-section--summary">
            <h2>White Button</h2>
            <pre><code>.cta-btn .cta-btn--white</code></pre>
            <button class="cta-btn cta-btn--white">Button</button>
            <ul>
                <li>White buttons on solid background colour are good on components like publication headers where link text, primary and secondary buttons would lose contrast.</li>
                <li>The colour contrast ratio between text and background colour is as follows: white button on solid background colour 14.42:1</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>


